<h3>Using the Search Form</h3>

<p>The ShopReel interface allows you to configure searches via a form with manual inputs or by importing an Excel file acting as a cache.</p>

<h5>Manual Input</h5>
<p>Use this tab to enter search parameters directly for a custom ShopReel run. Default values are provided for convenience, but you can adjust them as needed.</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>SerpAPI Key:</strong> Enter your private API key in the field provided.<br>
        <em>Note:</em> This key is required for ShopReel to access Google Maps data via SerpAPI.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Search Term:</strong> Specify the type of business or shop you want to search for (e.g., "Fly Fishing Shops", "Tackle Stores").<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>Fly Fishing Shops</code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Location:</strong> Enter latitude and longitude in decimal degrees. You can also click the map button to pick a location visually.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> Yellowstone National Park: <code>Latitude: 44.427963</code>, <code>Longitude: -110.588455</code>.<br>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Max Results:</strong> Set the maximum number of results to retrieve. ShopReel fetches results in batches of 20, so entering <code>101</code> could yield up to <code>120</code> results.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>100</code>.<br>
    </li>
</ul>

